<p><a name="References" id="References"></a></p>
<h2><span class="editsection">[<a href="/w/index.php?title=Uncertainty_principle&amp;action=edit&amp;section=21" title="Edit section: References">edit</a>]</span> <span class="mw-headline">References</span></h2>
<ul>
<li>W. Heisenberg, "Über den anschaulichen Inhalt der quantentheoretischen Kinematik und Mechanik", <i>Zeitschrift für Physik</i>, <b>43</b> 1927, pp. 172–198. English translation: J. A. Wheeler and H. Zurek, <i>Quantum Theory and Measurement</i> Princeton Univ. Press, 1983, pp. 62–84.</li>
<li><a href="/wiki/Leonid_Mandelshtam" title="Leonid Mandelshtam" class="mw-redirect">L. I. Mandelshtam</a>, <a href="/wiki/Igor_Tamm" title="Igor Tamm">I. E. Tamm</a> "<a href="http://daarb.narod.ru/mandtamm-eng.html" class="external text" title="http://daarb.narod.ru/mandtamm-eng.html" rel="nofollow">The uncertainty relation between energy and time in nonrelativistic quantum mechanics</a>", Izv. Akad. Nauk SSSR (ser. fiz.) <b>9</b>, 122-128 (1945). English translation: J. Phys. (USSR) <b>9</b>, 249-254 (1945).</li>
<li><cite style="font-style:normal" class="" id="CITEREFFollandSitaram.2C_Alladi1997">Folland, Gerald; Sitaram, Alladi (May 1997). "<a href="http://www.springerlink.com/content/f7492v6374716m4g/fulltext.pdf" class="external text" title="http://www.springerlink.com/content/f7492v6374716m4g/fulltext.pdf" rel="nofollow">The Uncertainty Principle: A Mathematical Survey</a>" (PDF). <i>Journal of Fourier Analysis and Applications</i> <b>3</b> (3): 207–238. <a href="/wiki/Digital_object_identifier" title="Digital object identifier">doi</a>:<span class="neverexpand"><a href="http://dx.doi.org/10.1007%2FBF02649110" class="external text" title="http://dx.doi.org/10.1007%2FBF02649110" rel="nofollow">10.1007/BF02649110</a></span>. <a href="/wiki/Mathematical_Reviews" title="Mathematical Reviews">MR</a><a href="http://www.ams.org/mathscinet-getitem?mr=98f:42006" class="external text" title="http://www.ams.org/mathscinet-getitem?mr=98f:42006" rel="nofollow">98f:42006</a><span class="printonly">. <a href="http://www.springerlink.com/content/f7492v6374716m4g/fulltext.pdf" class="external free" title="http://www.springerlink.com/content/f7492v6374716m4g/fulltext.pdf" rel="nofollow">http://www.springerlink.com/content/f7492v6374716m4g/fulltext.pdf</a></span>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.atitle=The+Uncertainty+Principle%3A+A+Mathematical+Survey&amp;rft.jtitle=Journal+of+Fourier+Analysis+and+Applications&amp;rft.aulast=Folland&amp;rft.aufirst=Gerald&amp;rft.au=Folland%2C+Gerald&amp;rft.au=Sitaram%2C+Alladi&amp;rft.date=May+1997&amp;rft.volume=3&amp;rft.issue=3&amp;rft.pages=207%E2%80%93238&amp;rft_id=info:doi/10.1007%2FBF02649110&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.springerlink.com%2Fcontent%2Ff7492v6374716m4g%2Ffulltext.pdf&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Uncertainty_principle"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
<li>Q. Zheng and T. Kobayashi, <i>Quantum Optics as a Relativistic Theory of Light</i>; Physics Essays 9 (1996) 447. Annual Report, Department of Physics, School of Science, University of Tokyo (1992) 240.</li>
</ul>
